                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id = "a1">
                      ‎<locus target = "#iiv"/>
                      <desc>
                      Fragment of a hymn to Mary. Insufficiently legible, with incipit <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ዘበሰለ፡(?) መኑ፡ ተኀጕለ። በጸሎኪ፡ ዘተወከለ፡ ፍቅርኪ፡ ኀየለ።...</foreign>
                      </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id = "a2">
                      <locus target = "#iiv #iiiv"/> Arabic words transliterated in Amharic letters. ‎
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id = "a3">
                      <desc>
                      ‎<locus target = "#iiir #iiiv"/> Prayer against the evil eye, <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ሕማመ፡ ዐይን፡</foreign>. Abbadie, 143, f. ‎‎49r, Conti Rossini, Notice, no. 109
                      with incipit <foreign xml:lang = "gez">በስመ፡ አብ፡...ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ እምሕማመ፡ ዓይን፡ እስመ፡፡መጻእኪ፡ ኀቤየ፡ ወእብለኪ፡ አይቴ፡ ተሐውሪ፡ ወትቤ፡ አሐውር፡ ኀበ፡ ዕበልዕ፡ ሥጋ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ መጥባሕ፡...</foreign>‎
                      </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id = "a4">
                      <locus target = "#iiiv"/> Death record, name and date insufficiently legible
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a5">
                        <locus target = "#110v"/> Greeting to the tongue, words and breath of the Archangel <name ref = "PRS8083Raphael"/>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a6">
                        ‎<locus target = "#168v"/>The lucky days of the year, <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ጽንዕት፡</foreign>, as opposed to the ‎unlucky days, <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ጽንጽንት</foreign>; cf. Abbadie 156, f. 19r, Conti Rossini, ‎Notice, no. 59; and Abbadie 186, f. 14v, Conti Rossini, Notice, no. ‎‎233.‎
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a7">
                        <locus target = "#169v"/> Medical prescription for an unspecified illness, ‎insufficiently legible.‎
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e1">
                        ‎<locus target = "#ir"/>: Rejected leaf with ኪ and ን in an eighteenth-century hand. ‎
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a8">
                        <locus target = "#96r"/> words from the text on the same folio copied in a crude hand
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a9">
                        <locus target = "#170r #170v"/> Unintelligible note
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e2">
                        The scribe rarely has to complete a line of text on another line. The challenge is addressed mainly through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. Where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (e.g., <locus target = "#7r #26r"/>, etc.)
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e3">
                        Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target = "#10r #76v #85r #90r #91r #95v #115v #116v #118r"/>, etc.);
                        and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target = "#99v #142r"/>);
                        and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target = "#136v"/>, line 6)
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                        The reinforcement strip sewn around quire seven is from a rejected leaf of another book and has text on it.
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "a10">
                        <desc type = "OwnershipNote">
                        Note of ownership by <foreign xml:lang = "gez">አባ፡ እማም፡</foreign> <locus target = "#iiiv"/>, and <foreign xml:lang = "gez">አባ፡ አለማየሁ፡</foreign> of Morät, <locus target = "#136v"/>
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e5">
                        <locus target = "#iir"/> blank
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id = "e6">
                        Columetric layout of text: <locus from = "#145v" to = "#146v"/> (tenth biblical canticle).
                      </item>
